            <div type="translation">
                <p>According to the will of Publius Gessius Primus, freedman of Publius; Gessia Fausta, freedwoman of Publius; Publius Gessius, son of Publius, of the Romilian tribe; Publius Gessius Primus, freedman of Publius. Under the direction of Gessia Fausta</p>
                
                
            </div>

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Line 3: First <hi rend="italic">I</hi> in <hi rend="italic">Primi</hi> is tall.</p>
                <p>Line 4: <hi rend="italic">Rom(ilia)</hi> Degrassi ILLRP. Tall <hi rend="italic">P</hi> in both instances of <hi rend="italic">Publius</hi> used as praenomen (4.15 and 4.28, but tallest in 4.28,  Primus’ praenomen), but not when used in filiation, libertination, or in <hi rend="italic">Primus</hi>. <hi rend="italic">I</hi> in <hi rend="italic">Primus</hi> is tall.</p>
                <p>Line 5: <hi rend="italic">Arbitr(atu)</hi> Degrassi ILLRP.</p>
                <p>Line 6: <hi rend="italic">Gessia</hi> Kleiner.</p>
                <p>Line 7: <hi rend="italic">Faustae</hi> Degrassi ILLRP; <hi rend="italic">Fausta</hi> Kleiner.</p>
                <p>Triangular punctuation marks between words, none at the ends of lines.</p>
